            <h2 style="color: #D20A11; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 25px;">Important Update: Australia Visa Application Fees</h2>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Dear Applicant,</p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">We would like to inform you about recent revisions to Australia's visa application fees, as announced by the Department of Home Affairs. These changes may affect your application planning.</p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Below is a summary of the revised fees for various visa subclasses, presented for your easy reference:</p>

            <!-- Modern Table for Fees -->
            <table class="modern-table" role="presentation">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>VISA TYPE</th>
                        <th>REVISED FEES</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Partner Visa (subclass 820/801 or 309/100)</td>
                        <td>$9,365 AUD</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Student Visa (subclass 500)</td>
                        <td>$2,000 AUD (previously $1,600)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Working Holiday Visa (subclass 417)</td>
                        <td>$670 AUD</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Visitor Visa (subclass 600)</td>
                        <td>Offshore – $200 AUD | Onshore – $500 AUD</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Temporary Skill Shortage - TSS (subclass 482)</td>
                        <td>$3,210 AUD</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Employer Nomination Scheme (subclass 186)</td>
                        <td>$4,910 AUD</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Skilled Employer Sponsored Regional (Provisional) – subclass 494</td>
                        <td>$4,910 AUD</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Skilled Independent visa (subclass 189)</td>
                        <td>$4,910 AUD</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Skilled Nominated visa (subclass 190)</td>
                        <td>$4,910 AUD</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>National Innovation Visa (subclass 858)</td>
                        <td>$4,910 AUD</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Training visa (subclass 407)</td>
                        <td>$430 AUD</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            <!-- End Modern Table for Fees -->

